    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
        <body>
            <div rend="parallel">
                <p xml:id="KT384-kilavi">“niṉ parattaiyarkku nī uṟṟa cūḷuṟavu naṉṟāy iruntatu” eṉṟu
                    nakaiyāṭit tōḻi vāyiṉ maṟuttatu. </p>


                <p xml:lang="en">The door refused by the confidante in jest,
                    saying “it is excellent to have the oath, which you have made to your other
                    women.” </p>
            </div>

            <div rend="parallel">
                <lg xml:id="KT384">
                    <l> uḻuntuṭaik kaḻutiṟ karumpuṭaip paṇaittō</l>
                    <l> ṇeṭumpal kūntaṟ kuṟuntoṭi makaḷir</l>
                    <l> nalaṉuṇṭu tuṟatti yāyiṉ</l>
                    <l> mikanaṉ ṟamma makiḻnaniṉ cūḷē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg xml:lang="en">
                    <l rend="indent"> If you give [her] up, having eaten [her] innocence,</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> [for] women with tight bracelets, long many tresses</l>
                    <l rend="indent8"> [and] bamboo shoulders</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> with sugarcane [drawing ], <note place="foot">Thus Cām.'s gloss,
                        backed up by a parallel in NA 39.11 as well as several passages in the <term xml:lang="ta">Kalittokai</term> (Kali 63.7f., 64.19, 76.15, 112.6,
                        143.31f.). Most explicit is perhaps Cilap. 2.29: <term xml:lang="ta">karumpum
                        valliyum peruntōḷ eḻuti </term> "drawing a sugarcane and a creeper on [her]
                        big shoulder".</note>  on the platform for [guarding]</l>
                    <l rend="indent8"> the black gram [field,</l>
                    <l> very good, alas, delightful man, [is] your oath.</l>

                    <lg type="alternate" sameAs="2+3b" resp="#TVG">
                        <l>If you give up, having eaten [their] innocence,</l>
                        <l>the women with tight bracelets ...</l>
                    </lg>
                </lg>
            </div>
